@startuml MobileDeviceAuth_SysMLv1_Architecture
' =============================================================================
' SysML v1 (PlantUML) -- Mobile Device Authentication with Concurrent WiFi
' Second worked example from
' "2026-06-22-ProposalForCASCaRAExtension.docx" (Part 2, Example 2).
' Companion to: MobileDeviceAuth_SysMLv2.sysml
'
' Uses the working-group-agreed vocabulary:
'   ItemFlow (root) with 4 direct specializations
'   FunctionPort with security attributes
'   Actor hierarchy + Source / Sink roles
' =============================================================================
title bdd -- MobileDevice (Authentication + concurrent WiFi)

skinparam class {
    BackgroundColor #FFF8E1
    BorderColor     #7A6100
    ArrowColor      #333333
}

' ---- InformationFlow specializations with security attributes ----------

class Password <<block, InformationFlow>> {
    +bytes                   : 32
    +protocolStr             : "TLS 1.3"
    +securityClassification  : "Confidential"
    +integrityLevelSpec      : "ASIL-B"
}
class AuthToken <<block, InformationFlow>> {
    +bytes                   : 256
    +protocolStr             : "OAuth2"
    +privilegeLevel          : "Enhanced"
    +securityClassification  : "Confidential"
}
class WiFiPayload <<block, InformationFlow>> {
    +protocolStr             : "IEEE 802.11"
    +securityContext         : "Isolated"
    +integrityLevelSpec      : "QM"
}

' ---- Mobile device (system boundary) + 3 internal Functions -----------

class MobileDevice <<SystemBoundary>> {
    +authenticate    : AuthenticateBlock
    +grantPrivileges : GrantPrivilegesBlock
    +wifi            : WiFiTransceiveBlock
}
class AuthenticateBlock <<Function>> {
    +pwIn     : FunctionPort <<in>>
    +tokenOut : FunctionPort <<out>>
    +behavior : Authenticate()
}
class GrantPrivilegesBlock <<Function>> {
    +tokenIn  : FunctionPort <<in>>
    +behavior : GrantPrivileges()
}
class WiFiTransceiveBlock <<Function>> {
    +wifi     : FunctionPort <<inout>>
    +behavior : WiFiTransceive()
}
MobileDevice *-- AuthenticateBlock
MobileDevice *-- GrantPrivilegesBlock
MobileDevice *-- WiFiTransceiveBlock

' ---- External Actors (Actor sub-kind + flow role) ---------------------

class HumanUser <<User, Source>>
class WiFiPeer  <<ExternalSystem, Source, Sink>>

' ---- Flow A -- Confidential authentication chain ----------------------

HumanUser            ..> AuthenticateBlock    : "«InformationFlow» Password\nsecurityClassification=Confidential"
AuthenticateBlock    ..> GrantPrivilegesBlock : "«InformationFlow» AuthToken\nprivilegeLevel=Enhanced"

' ---- Flow B -- Isolated WiFi payload (concurrent, bidirectional) ------

WiFiPeer             ..> WiFiTransceiveBlock  : "«InformationFlow» WiFiPayload\nprotocol=IEEE 802.11, securityContext=Isolated"
WiFiTransceiveBlock  ..> WiFiPeer             : "«InformationFlow» WiFiPayload (return)"

note bottom of MobileDevice
  Two concurrent flows sharing one
  system boundary but in DIFFERENT
  security contexts.

  CASCaRA (today) cannot express
  either the flow items or their
  security attributes.

  With the proposal (ItemFlow +
  FunctionPort + Actor Source/Sink)
  every attribute above is
  representable.
end note

@enduml
